news.title: New Delhi: NDMC collects Rs 1,045 crore property tax in FY25
news.para: Till March 30, 2025, the council had collected Rs 1,045 crore. After the system updates payments received till March 31, the total collection is expected to reach Rs 1,050 crore, according to officials.

news.title: Gurugram: OCs of 750 more homes in DLF areas to be revoked for flouting building code
news.para: The move follows previous actions where DTCP already sought OC cancellations of 1,588 houses, bringing the total number of properties under scrutiny to 2,431.

news.title: Three more cases filed against Ansal API in Lucknow
news.para: While a woman accused the company of defrauding her of Rs 6.15 crore in the name of investment in land, two other persons alleged that they were defrauded of about Rs 50 lakh in the name of plots and flats.

news.title: Home-buyers in Karnataka seek CBI probe as 2,678 projects remain incomplete
news.para: According to the K-RERA website, a whopping number of housing projects’ completion dates have expired. The K-RERA website stated that 2,678 housing projects failed to complete as per the schedule.

news.title: Ready reckoner hike to prompt developers, societies to rework redevelopment pacts
news.para: The increase in ready reckoner rates by the Maharashtra government is influencing realty developers and housing societies in Mumbai and Thane to reassess redevelopment contracts. With redevelopment activities surging, the rise in rates necessitates renegotiations to manage escalating costs and ensure financial viability.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 395 crore assets of Three C Shelters, promoters in Gurugram
news.para: Additionally, equity shares worth Rs 108 crore in G4S Secure Solutions (India) Pvt Ltd — linked to another promoter Vidur Bharadwaj — have also been attached by ED's zonal office.

news.title: Rocket Companies to buy Mr Cooper Group for $9.4 billion
news.para: Better home inventory and recent declines in long-term bond yields are bringing back potential buyers to the housing market after years of struggle due to high interest rates and prices.

news.title: Panaji's dust-free road promise fails as IPSCDL misses deadline
news.para: Several roads in the city remain dug up after being tarred, particularly the main M G Road. Meanwhile, work to lay the final section of the sewerage network at Taad Maad, St Inez remains, well, work in progress.

news.title: Australia home prices rise 0.4%in March after rate cut: CoreLogic data
news.para: The monthly rise was broad-based, with every capital city posting a positive chance except for Hobart. Prices in Sydney rose 0.3% while Melbourne gained 0.5%.

news.title: British house prices fall 0.2% in March: Nationwide
news.para: As of Tuesday, Britain's government has lowered the price threshold at which buyers become eligible to pay property transaction taxes - known as stamp duty.

news.title: Man Industries' subsidiary grants development rights of Navi Mumbai land to Paradise Group
news.para: The company will get upfront amount of ₹70 crore and 30% area i.e. equivalent to approximately 4,50,000 sq ft carpet area out of total area of the developed property, which has a monetising value of about ₹650 – ₹700 crore over a period of 5-6 years.

news.title: Tripura's first high-rise earthquake-resistant building nears completion
news.para: "The main purpose of constructing this G+14 building using advanced technology is to bring all the directorate offices of the Tripura government into one place.

news.title: Ramco Cements disposed assets worth Rs 455 crore to reduce debt
news.para: In November last year, The Ramco Cements informed about its proposal of disposal of non-core assets with a targeted value of about ₹1,000 crore and using proceeds for paring debts.

news.title: Ready reckoners rise by 4.3% in Nagpur from April 1
news.para: In Nagpur, there is an average increase of 4.23% in the localities within the municipal corporation's limits and 6.60% in pockets within the Nagpur Metropolitan Region Development Authority (NMRDA).

news.title: Mumbai-based Runwal Enterprises files DRHP for ₹1,000 crore IPO
news.para: Runwal Enterprises may consider a pre-IPO placement of specified securities, aggregating to ₹200 crore as pre-IPO placement shall not exceed 20% of the size of the fresh issue. If such placement is completed, the fresh issue size will be reduced.

news.title: Deadline of pending smart city projects in Thiruvananthapuram to be extended till December
news.para: The additional time will be utilised to complete major pending projects, including the renovation of the Palayam Connemara Market, development of Chalai Market and the construction of multi-level car parking (MLCP) facilities.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body receives Rs 100 crore property tax on March 31
news.para: This historic accomplishment also enabled GHMC to cross 2,000 crore in property tax collection for the first time in its history.

news.title: IndiQube gets SEBI nod for ₹850-crore IPO
news.para: According to the DRHP, the proposed IPO is combination of a fresh issue of equity shares aggregating up to ₹750 crore and an offer for sale (OFS) of equity shares aggregating up to ₹100 crore.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body crosses Rs 150 crore property tax target in FY25
news.para: ​​​By Monday, officials succeeded in recovering around Rs 152 crore from all four zones in property tax. The figure will increase when manual recovery by field staff is taken into account.

news.title: Ranchi civic body sets record with Rs 80.64 crore property tax collection
news.para: A significant portion of the tax came from door-to-door visits during which over Rs 41.81 crore was collected from 1,06,019 taxpayers.
